\section{Pharma conventions}{

Standard pharma submission tables (ICH E3, FDA/EMA) typically use one blank
line after titles and before footnotes. The package defaults reflect a
minimal layout:
\itemize{
\item \code{titles_after = 1L} — one blank line after titles
\item \code{footnotes_before = 1L} — one blank line before footnotes
\item \code{pagehead_after = 0L} — no gap (user decides)
\item \code{pagefoot_before = 0L} — no gap (user decides)
\item \code{page_by_after = 1L} — one blank line after page-by label
}
}

\section{YAML configuration}{

All five spacing values can be set in \verb{_tlframe.yml}:

